ðŸ‘‰ Want me to also draft the **GitHub Action YAML** (so every time you push code, the agents run automatically and update `ledger.json`)? That would make it feel *alive* to anyone visiting your repo.
Perfect â€” hereâ€™s a GitHub Actions workflow you can drop into .github/workflows/run_agents.yml.
This will run agents.py automatically every time you push code, and it will save the output ledger.json as an artifact (downloadable from the Actions tab).
â¸»
.github/workflows/run_agents.yml
name: Run Agents Prototype
on:
push:
branches: [ "main" ]
pull_request:
branches: [ "main" ]
jobs:
run-agents:
runs-on: ubuntu-latest
steps:
- name: Checkout repository
uses: actions/checkout@v3
- name: Set up Python
uses: actions/setup-python@v4
with:
python-version: "3.10"
- name: Install dependencies
run: |
python -m pip install --upgrade pip
if [ -f requirements.txt ]; then pip install -r requirements.txt; fi
- name: Run agents.py
run: |
python agents.py
- name: Upload ledger.json
uses: actions/upload-artifact@v3
with:
name: ledger
path: ledger.json
â¸»
ðŸ”‘ What this does
â€¢Â Â Â Triggers on every push to main or PR.
â€¢Â Â Â Sets up Python 3.10 on the GitHub runner.
â€¢Â Â Â Runs your agents.py.
â€¢Â Â Â Saves ledger.json as an artifact attached to the run.
â¸»
