1. Add a VERSION file at repo root
This keeps the current version explicit and tracked in Git.
0.1.0
â¸»
2. New Workflow: .github/workflows/release.yml
name: Semantic Release
on:
push:
branches: [ "main" ]
jobs:
release:
runs-on: ubuntu-latest
steps:
- name: Checkout repository
uses: actions/checkout@v3
with:
fetch-depth: 0
- name: Set up Git
run: |
git config user.name "github-actions[bot]"
git config user.email "41898282+github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com"
- name: Get last commit message
id: commitmsg
run: echo "msg=$(git log -1 --pretty=%s)" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT
- name: Read current version
id: current
run: echo "version=$(cat VERSION)" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT
- name: Bump version
id: bump
run: |
old=${{ steps.current.outputs.version }}
IFS='.' read -r major minor patch <<< "$old"
msg="${{ steps.commitmsg.outputs.msg }}"
if [[ $msg == feat:* ]]; then
minor=$((minor+1))
patch=0
elif [[ $msg == fix:* ]]; then
patch=$((patch+1))
else
patch=$((patch+1))
fi
new="$major.$minor.$patch"
echo "new=$new" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT
echo "$new" > VERSION
- name: Commit and tag new version
run: |
git add VERSION
git commit -m "chore: bump version to ${{ steps.bump.outputs.new }}"
git tag -a "v${{ steps.bump.outputs.new }}" -m "Release v${{ steps.bump.outputs.new }}"
git push
git push --tags
- name: Create GitHub Release
uses: softprops/action-gh-release@v1
with:
tag_name: v${{ steps.bump.outputs.new }}
name: Release v${{ steps.bump.outputs.new}}
body: |
Automated release triggered by commit:
${{ steps.commitmsg.outputs.msg }}
â¸»
3. How It Works
â€¢Â Â Â Reads current version from VERSION.
â€¢Â Â Â Bumps it automatically based on last commit:
â€¢Â Â Â feat: â†’ minor bump (0.1.0 â†’ 0.2.0).
â€¢Â Â Â fix: â†’ patch bump (0.1.0 â†’ 0.1.1).
â€¢Â Â Â Other (docs:, test:, chore:) â†’ patch bump.
â€¢Â Â Â Commits the updated VERSION file.
â€¢Â Â Â Creates a Git tag (v0.2.0).
â€¢Â Â Â Publishes a GitHub Release for visibility.
â¸»
4. Example in Action
â€¢Â Â Â Commit: feat: add contradiction detection tool
â€¢Â Â Â VERSION: 0.1.0 â†’ 0.2.0
â€¢Â Â Â Tag: v0.2.0
â€¢Â Â Â GitHub Release created.
â€¢Â Â Â Commit: fix: handle empty ledger.json
â€¢Â Â Â VERSION: 0.2.0 â†’ 0.2.1
â€¢Â Â Â Tag: v0.2.1
â¸»
ðŸ”‘ Why This Matters
â€¢Â Â Â Closes the governance loop: every change bumps a version automatically.
â€¢Â Â Â Professional polish: all serious projects use semantic versioning.
â€¢Â Â Â Automation-driven: no manual bookkeeping â€” commits drive releases.
â€¢Â Â Â Public signal: visitors see active version tags and releases, proving project momentum.
â¸»
