Today weâ€™re releasing Tessrax v1.0.0, an open-source governance engine that metabolizes contradictions.
Our pilot: Corporate ESG Reports vs Earnings Calls.
Companies promise sustainability, equity, and transparency in glossy ESG reports. Then, in quarterly earnings calls, they admit to layoffs, fossil fuel expansion, or withholding metrics. Tessrax sits between these worlds â€” surfacing contradictions and logging them immutably.
What Tessrax Does
â€¢Â Â Â Ingests reports & transcripts (PDF/HTML/TXT).
â€¢Â Â Â Extracts claims into analyzable units.
â€¢Â Â Â Maps contradictions across sources with LLM analysis.
â€¢Â Â Â Audits them for validity & confidence.
â€¢Â Â Â Logs them with timestamp + hash in an immutable ledger.
â€¢Â Â Â Visualizes them live on a dashboard (Environment / Social / Governance).
Why It Matters
Governance isnâ€™t just about what is claimed â€” itâ€™s about contradictions between claims and actions. Tessrax makes those contradictions visible, auditable, and undeniable.
In our benchmark, Tessrax achieved an F1 score of 0.74, proving that even through corporate jargon, truth gaps can be quantified.
Whatâ€™s Next
â€¢Â Â Â Expand beyond ESG: DAOs, law, AI governance.
â€¢Â Â Â Stronger semantic contradiction classification.
â€¢Â Â Â Real-time ingestion of governance streams.
