â¸»

ðŸ“œ Tessrax Sentry Engine â€“ Foundation Plan

1. Core Inputs
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â charter.json â†’ Explicit rules, promises, or commitments written in machine-readable form.
Example:

{
  "pii_policy": {
    "description": "No PII should appear in logs.",
    "pattern": "(\\b[A-Z0-9._%+-]+@[A-Z0-9.-]+\\.[A-Z]{2,}\\b)|(\\b\\d{16}\\b)",
    "severity": "critical"
  },
  "approval_policy": {
    "description": "Transactions > $10k require 2 approvals.",
    "rule_type": "transaction",
    "threshold": 10000,
    "approvals_required": 2
  }
}


Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â event_stream.jsonl (or real-time API/WebSocket feed) â†’ Structured events as they occur.
Example log entry:

{"timestamp": "2025-10-02T12:30:15Z", "type": "log", "message": "User john@example.com logged in"}



â¸»

2. Engine Logic

At its heart, TSE is a real-time contradiction detector:
	1.	Parse Charter rules.
	2.	Continuously ingest events.
	3.	Apply rule-specific checkers: regex for PII, counters for approvals, filters for project tags.
	4.	When a contradiction is found â†’ emit a contradiction receipt.

Example receipt:

{
  "timestamp": "2025-10-02T12:30:20Z",
  "rule": "pii_policy",
  "event": {"type": "log", "message": "User john@example.com logged in"},
  "violation": "PII Leak Contradiction: Email found in logs."
}


â¸»

3. Outputs
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â ledger.jsonl â†’ Immutable append-only log of contradictions.
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â alerts/ â†’ Optional integrations (Slack, email, SIEM forwarders).
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â dashboard/ â†’ A lightweight dashboard (Flask/FastAPI + D3.js) to visualize contradictions live.

â¸»

4. Architecture (MVP â†’ Enterprise)

MVP:
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â CLI tool: python sentry.py --charter charter.json --stream event_stream.jsonl
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â Checks rules and writes to ledger.

Phase 2:
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â Real-time ingestion from Kafka/WebSocket.
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â Configurable sinks (database, Elasticsearch, Splunk).

Phase 3:
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â Cloud-native deployment (Docker + Kubernetes).
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â Streaming dashboards, audit-friendly export formats.

â¸»

5. Use Cases (Positioning)
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â Compliance â†’ PCI/PII leaks in logs.
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â Finance â†’ Approval workflows monitored in real time.
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â Engineering Strategy â†’ Alignment of live commits with stated priorities.

â¸»

ðŸš€ Why Itâ€™s Powerful
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â Meta Leap: From static text audit â†’ dynamic, behavioral audit.
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â Proof of Governance Philosophy: Intent vs. action contradiction detection at scale.
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â Massive Market Fit: Every company has compliance promises and event logs. None currently have a living contradiction engine standing sentry over them.

