Do you want me to also scaffold a GitHub Actions workflow YAML that runs pytest, then ci_report.py, and uploads dashboard.html as a CI artifact (so you can download/view it after each run)?

-Tessrax LLC-

GPT to Joshâ€”

Hereâ€™s the GitHub Actions workflow you asked for. It runs your full test pipeline, executes the stress harness, and publishes dashboard.html as a downloadable artifact on every push or pull request.

â¸»

.github/workflows/ci.yml

name: Tessrax CI

on:
  push:
    branches: [ "main" ]
  pull_request:
    branches: [ "main" ]

jobs:
  build-and-test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
    - name: Checkout repository
      uses: actions/checkout@v4

    - name: Set up Python
      uses: actions/setup-python@v5
      with:
        python-version: '3.11'

    - name: Install dependencies
      run: |
        python -m venv .venv
        source .venv/bin/activate
        pip install --upgrade pip
        pip install -r requirements.txt
        pip install pytest pytest-cov psutil

    - name: Run unit + integration tests
      run: |
        source .venv/bin/activate
        pytest --maxfail=1 --disable-warnings -q --cov=core --cov=compliance_auditor

    - name: Run stress tests and build dashboard
      run: |
        source .venv/bin/activate
        python ci_report.py

    - name: Upload dashboard artifact
      uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
      with:
        name: stress-dashboard
        path: dashboard.html


â¸»

What this does
	1.	Checks out repo â†’ ensures the workflow has your files.
	2.	Sets up Python 3.11 (you can change version).
	3.	Installs deps from requirements.txt + adds pytest, pytest-cov, psutil.
	4.	Runs all tests â†’ fails CI if coverage/tests donâ€™t pass.
	5.	Runs stress harness (ci_report.py) â†’ regenerates dashboard.html.
	6.	Uploads dashboard â†’ artifact appears in the CI run logs, downloadable with one click.

â¸»

With this in place:
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â Every commit to main or PR triggers tests + stress trials.
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â Youâ€™ll get green/red test results + resilience dashboard artifact automatically.
Â Â Â â€¢Â Â Â Universality isnâ€™t just conceptualâ€”itâ€™s enforced in CI.

